    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - LIGHT SYSTEMS - TROUBLESHOOTING - Stop Light
        Switch, Tractor, or Truck With 4-Wheel Connections, With Air Brakes and International Engine
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="x0824030" svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Stop Light Switch, Tractor, or Truck With 4-Wheel Connections, With Air Brakes and International Engine
        </title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>For troubleshooting brake switch circuit input signals to the engine ECM, refer to the Engine
                    Diagnostic Manual.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <table id="t0824030" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Stop Light Switch, Tractor, or Truck With 4-Wheel Trailer Connections, With Air Brakes and
                International Engine
            </title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.54in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.54in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.74in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.82in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.78in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.68in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.61in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove fuse F9 and check for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>F9</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At F9, measure voltage from circuit 14A to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>F9, 14A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 14A, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect stop light switch conn. (46) or (11) and measure voltage from circuit 70 to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(46) or (11), 70 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 70, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At (46) or (11), measure resistance of stop light switch and wiring from red wire to
                                brown wire with brake pedal applied.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(46) or (11), red to brown wire.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to Step 7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect stop light switch connector (71). Measure resistance of red and brown wires
                                between switch and connector (46) or (11).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(46) or (11) to (71), red and brown wires.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in red or brown wire(s), then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Measure resistance across terminals of stop light switch (71) with brakes applied.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(71), across term.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace stop light switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (46) or (11) and stop light switch connectors if applicable.
                                Disconnect turn signal relay (660). With brake applied and at relay socket, measure
                                voltage from circuit 70E, cavity A/5, to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(660), 70E, cav. A/5 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 70E/70DS, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At relay socket (660), measure voltage from circuit 70A, cavity E/1 to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(660), 70A, cav. E/1 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 70A, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At relay socket (660), measure resistance from circuit 97-GH, cavity B/2 to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(660), 97-GH, cav. B/2 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 97-GH/11-GN, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At relay socket, install jumper from circuit 70B, cavity C/4 to ground. Disconnect
                                turn signal conn. (459) and measure resistance from circuit 70B, cavity B to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(459), 70B, cav. B, to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 70B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove jumper and install relay. With brakes applied and at (459), measure voltage
                                from circuit 70B to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(459), 70B, cav. B, to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect turn signal conn. (459). Stop light circuits check good. If condition
                                persists, refer to Turn Signal Troubleshooting in CAB ACCESSORIES section.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
